---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Hypothesis Roadmap">
  <main id="myContent" class="content">
    <div class="newspaper" id="H-Container">
      <div class="DropCap intro nobreak">Hypothesis testing is a fundamental part of the scientific process where it is used to evaluate whether something being hypothesized is statistically valid or not.</div>
      <div class="DropCap intro nobreak" id="H-Def">Hypothesis testing is so named because the user has <span class="highlight">hypothesized</span> about something and wants statistical evedence of the validity (or lack thereof) of The hypothesis. A Null Hypothesis (H<sub>0</sub>) and an Alternate Hypothesis (H<sub>A</sub>) are key element of every test. The nature of H<sub>0</sub> is always based on the variation observed in the data being purely random (or "Nothing interesting going on") and H<sub>A</sub> is based on something else is going on. H<sub>0</sub> and H<sub>A</sub> are always defined (at least in general) by the specific test being run and are not selectable by the user. The tests all provide a "p" statistic that represents The probability that H<sub>0</sub> is <span class="highlight">TRUE</span>. Decisions are ususally made based on P statistics and the value of p to use as the cutoff shoud be a carefully considered business decision. Typically, a value of .05 (5%) is used where if p is less that .05, H<sub>0</sub> is rejected and it is assumed that H<sub>A</sub> is correct. Test selection is a function of the specifics of the data collected.</div>
    </div>
    <h1>Roadmap for selecting Hypothesis testing tools</h1>
    <div class="roadmap" id="h-roadmap">
      <div class="mapQuestion">Type of data?</div>
      <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b1" onclick="toggleElement()">Attribute<span class="tooltiptext">Discrete:
          Items are generally counted</span></button>
      <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b2" onclick="toggleElement()">Variable<span class="tooltiptext">Continuous:
          Items are generally measured</span></button>
      <div class="MapLine" id='1'>
        <div class="mapQuestion">Attribute: Number of Factors?</div>
        <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b11" onclick="toggleElement()">1<span class="tooltiptext">Looking at only
            one attribute</span></button>
        <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b12" onclick="toggleElement()">2<span class="tooltiptext">Looking at 2 or
            more attributes</span></button>
        <div class=" MapLine" id="11">
          <div class="mapQuestion">Number of samples?</div>
          <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b111" onclick="toggleElement()">1<span class="tooltiptext">Only one type
              of item - compare against a standard</span></button>
          <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b112" onclick="toggleElement()">2<span class="tooltiptext">2 types of
              items - compare against each other</span></button>
          <div class="MapLine" id="111">
            <div class="HypoTable">
              <div class="HTableName">1-Proportion Test</div>
              <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: P<sub>1</sub> = P<sub>t</sub></div>
              <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: P<sub>1</sub> &#8800 P<sub>t</sub></div>
              <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
              <div class="HTabUseCase">Test if the proportion (percent) of the population for a specific type of article
                (e.g. brand, color, material, etc.) meets a specification (e.g. 90% 0f parts must pass a test).</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="MapLine" id="112">
            <div class="HypoTable">
              <div class="HTableName">2-Proportion Test</div>
              <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: P<sub>1</sub> = P<sub>2</sub></div>
              <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: P<sub>1</sub> &#8800 P<sub>2</sub></div>
              <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
              <div class="HTabUseCase">Test if the proportion (percent) of the population for two specific types of
                articles (e.g. brand, color, material, etc.) are equal (e.g. the odds of A and B are the same).</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="MapLine" id="12">
          <div class="HypoTable">
            <div class="HTableName">Contingency Table</div>
            <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: F<sub>A</sub> and F<sub>B</sub> are independant</div>
            <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: F<sub>A</sub> and F<sub>B</sub> are dependant</div>
            <div class="HTabLink"><a class="W-Ref" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contingency_table"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt=""></a></div>
            <div class="HTabUseCase">Test ...</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="MapLine" id="2">
        <div class="mapQuestion">Number of factors?</div>
        <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21" onclick="toggleElement()">1<span class="tooltiptext">Looking at a
            single attribute</span></button>
        <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b22" onclick="toggleElement()">More than 1<span
            class="tooltiptext">Looking at 2 or more attributes</span></button>
        <div class="MapLine" accesskey="" id="21">
          <div class="mapQuestion">Is data Normal or Non-Normal?</div>
          <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b211" onclick="toggleElement()">Normal<span class="tooltiptext">The data
              is normally distributed</span></button>
          <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b212" onclick="toggleElement()">Not Normal<span class="tooltiptext">The
              data is not normally distributed (e.g. skewed)</span></button>
          <div class="MapLine" id="211">
            <div class="mapQuestion">Number of Levels?</div>
            <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b2111" onclick="toggleElement()">1<span class="tooltiptext">A single
                type of item (e.g. brand, material, color, etc)</span></button>
            <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b2112" onclick="toggleElement()">2<span class="tooltiptext">Two types
                of items (e.g. brand, material, color, etc)</span></button>
            <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b2113" onclick="toggleElement()">More than 2<span
                class="tooltiptext">Three or more types of items (e.g. brand, material, color, etc)</span></button>
            <div class="MapLine" id="2111">
              <div class="mapQuestion">Type of Test for 1 Level?</div>
              <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21111" onclick="toggleElement()">Mean<span
                  class="tooltiptext">Checking average value against a specification</span></button>
              <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21112" onclick="toggleElement()">Standard Deviation<span
                  class="tooltiptext">Checking variation against a standard</span></button>
              <div class="MapLine" id="21112">
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">Chi<sup>2</sup>Test</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &sigma;<sub>1</sub> = &sigma;<sub>t</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &sigma;<sub>1</sub> &#8800 &sigma;<sub>t</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><a class="W-Ref" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chi-squared_test"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt=""></a>
                  </div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Determine if the variation for a specific type meets a specifaction -
                    generally a maximum.</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="MapLine" id="21111">
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">1 Sample t Test</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &mu;<sub>1</sub> = &mu;<sub>t</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &mu;<sub>1</sub> &#8800 &mu;<sub>t</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><a class="W-Ref" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Student%27s_t-test"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt=""></a>
                  </div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Determine if the avarage value for a specific type is within specifications
                    (e.g. thickness within +/- spec limits)</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="MapLine" id="2112">
              <div class="mapQuestion">Type of Test for 2 Levels?</div>
              <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21121" onclick="toggleElement()">Mean<span
                  class="tooltiptext">Checking average values</span></button>
              <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21122" onclick="toggleElement()">Standard Deviation<span
                  class="tooltiptext">Checking variation</span></button>
              <div class="MapLine" id="21122">
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">F Test</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &sigma;<sub>1</sub> = &sigma;<sub>2</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &sigma;<sub>1</sub> &#8800 &sigma;<sub>2</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Determine if variation for two different types is equal</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="MapLine" id="21121">
                <div class="mapQuestion">Is data independant?</div>
                <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b211211" onclick="toggleElement()">Independant<span
                    class="tooltiptext">Type B is unrelated to type A</span></button>
                <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b211212" onclick="toggleElement()">Dependant<span
                    class="tooltiptext">Types A and B are related (e.g. for a pair of shoes, a=left,
                    B=right)</span></button>
                <div class="MapLine" id="211211">
                  <div class="HypoTable">
                    <div class="HTableName">2 Sample t Test</div>
                    <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &mu;<sub>1</sub> = &mu;<sub>2</sub></div>
                    <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &mu;<sub>1</sub> &ne; &mu;<sub>2</sub></div>
                    <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                    <div class="HTabUseCase">Test if the avarage value for an attribute is the same for two specific
                      types of items</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="MapLine" id="211212">
                  <div class="HypoTable">
                    <div class="HTableName">Paired t Test</div>
                    <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &mu;<sub>1</sub> = &mu;<sub>2</sub></div>
                    <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &mu;<sub>1</sub> &#8800 &mu;<sub>2</sub></div>
                    <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                    <div class="HTabUseCase">Test if the average values for two specific types of items is the same when
                      subjected to the same conditions (e.g. is shoe sole wear the same for the left and right shoes?)
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="MapLine" id="2113">
              <div class="HypoTable">
                <div class="HTableName">Bartlets Test</div>
                <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &sigma;<sub>1</sub> = &sigma;<sub>2</sub> = &sigma;<sub>3</sub>
                </div>
                <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &sigma;<sub>i</sub> &#8800; &sigma;<sub>j</sub> for i &#8800; j
                  (or at least one is different)</div>
                <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                <div class="HTabUseCase">Test if three or more specific types of items the same average values</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Not Normal -->
          <div class="MapLine" id="212">
            <div class="mapQuestion">Number of levels?</div>
            <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b2121" onclick="toggleElement()">1<span class="tooltiptext">Single
                type of item</span></button>
            <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b2122" onclick="toggleElement()">2 or more<span
                class="tooltiptext">More than one type of item</span></button>
            <!-- 1 level -->
            <div class="MapLine" id="2121">
              <div class="mapQuestion">Test Type?</div>
              <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21211" onclick="toggleElement()">Median<span
                  class="tooltiptext">Test for central tendancy</span></button>
              <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21212" onclick="toggleElement()">Standard Deviation<span
                  class="tooltiptext">Test for variation</span></button>
              <!-- Test for Median -->
              <div class="MapLine" id="21211">
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">1-sample Wilcoxon or 1-Sample Significance</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: M<sub>1</sub> = M<sub>t</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: M<sub>1</sub> &#8800; M<sub>t</sub> (t = target)</div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Test if the median value for a set of non-normally distributed data meets a
                    specification</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="MapLine" id="21212">
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">Chi<sup>2</sup> Test</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &sigma;<sub>1</sub> = &sigma;<sub>t</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &sigma;<sub>1</sub> &#8800; &sigma;<sub>t</sub> (t = target)
                  </div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Test if the variation for a set of non-normally distributed data meets a
                    specification</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- 2 or more levels -->
            <div class="MapLine" id="2122">
              <div class="HypoTable">
                <div class="HTableName">Levene's Test</div>
                <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &sigma;<sub>1</sub> = &sigma;<sub>2</sub> = &sigma;<sub>3</sub> ...
                </div>
                <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &sigma;<sub>i</sub> &#8800; &sigma;<sub>j</sub> for i &#8800; j (or
                  at least 1 is different)</div>
                <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                <div class="HTabUseCase">Test if central tendancies for 2 or more specific types of items are the same
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mapQuestion">Test Results?</div>
              <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21221" onclick="toggleElement()">Reject H<sub>0</sub><span
                  class="tooltiptext">Central tendancies are not the same</span></button>
              <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b21222" onclick="toggleElement()">Fail to Reject H<sub>0</sub><span
                  class="tooltiptext">Central tendancies are the same</span></button>
              <div class="MapLine" id="21221">
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">2 Sample t Test</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: &mu;<sub>1</sub> = &mu;<sub>t</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: &mu;<sub>1</sub> &ne; &mu;<sub>t</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Test ...</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="MapLine" id="21222">
                <div class="mapQuestion">Number of Levels?</div>
                <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b212221" onclick="toggleElement()">2<span class="tooltiptext">Tool
                    tip</span></button>
                <button class="MapButton tooltip" id="b212222" onclick="toggleElement()">More than 2<span
                    class="tooltiptext">Tool tip</span></button>
              </div>
              <div class="MapLine" id="212221">
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">Mann-Whitney Test</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: M<sub>1</sub> = M<sub>2</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: M<sub>1</sub> &ne; M<sub>2</sub></div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Test ...</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="MapLine" id="212222">
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">Moods Median Test (used with outlier)</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: M<sub>1</sub> = M<sub>2</sub> = M<sub>3</sub>...</div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: M<sub>i</sub> &ne; M<sub>j</sub> for i&ne;j (or at least 1 is
                    different)</div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Test ...</div>
                </div>
                <div class="HypoTable">
                  <div class="HTableName">Kruskal-Wallis Test (used with no outlier)</div>
                  <div class="HTableH0">H<sub>0</sub>: M<sub>1</sub> = M<sub>2</sub> = M<sub>3</sub>...</div>
                  <div class="HTableHA">H<sub>A</sub>: M<sub>i</sub> &ne; M<sub>j</sub> for i&ne;j (or at least 1 is
                    different)</div>
                  <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
                  <div class="HTabUseCase">Test ...</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="MapLine" id="22">
          <div class="HypoTable">
            <div class="HTableName">ANOVA or Multiple Regression</div>
            <div class="HTableH0"></div>
            <div class="HTableHA"></div>
            <div class="HTabLink"><img src="../public/W-Logo.png" alt="Wikapedia Entry"></div>
            <div class="HTabUseCase">Test ...</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>